fields.title: Tools for Christian Living
fields.description:
Practical biblical principles for daily living.	

James 1:22-25 (CSB) - “But be doers of the word and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves.”
fields.subtitle: Facing and solving life's daily challenges with faith.

fields.title: The Foundations of Faith
fields.description:
Understanding the core beliefs of the Christian faith.	

Hebrews 11:1 (CSB) - “Now faith is the reality of what is hoped for, the proof of what is not seen.”

fields.title: Navigating Emotions with Faith
fields.description:
Managing emotions like fear, anxiousness, anger, jealously, bitterness, sadness, regret, and sorrow through faith.	

Psalm 34:18 (CSB) - “The Lord is near the brokenhearted; he saves those crushed in spirit.”

fields.title: Sharing Your Faith
fields.description:
Evangelism and witnessing in everyday life.	

Matthew 28:19-20 (CSB) - “Go, therefore, and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, teaching them to observe everything I have commanded you.”

fields.title: Marriage Built to Last
fields.description:
Strengthening marriages based on biblical principles.	

Ephesians 4:32: "Be kind and compassionate to one another, forgiving each other, just as in Christ God forgave you."

fields.title: The Power of Prayer
fields.description:
Through prayer, Christians can deepen their understanding of faith.

Philippians 4:6 - "Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving let your requests be made known to God."

fields.title: Tools for the Workplace
fields.subtitle: Living with faith in a multi-cultural work environment.
